<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Yang_Dong-geun" title="Yang Dong-geun">Yang Dong-geun</a> as Choi Bae-dal, the main character who becomes a master of karate (based on the real life karateka <a href="/wiki/Masutatsu_Oyama" class="mw-redirect" title="Masutatsu Oyama">Masutatsu Oyama</a>).</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Masaya_Kato" title="Masaya Kato">Masaya Kato</a> as Kato, the head of the Japanese Karate Association and, due to his <a href="/wiki/Xenophobia" title="Xenophobia">xenophobia</a>, enemy of Bae-dal.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Aya_Hirayama" title="Aya Hirayama">Aya Hirayama</a> as Yoko, a young <a href="/wiki/Japan" title="Japan">Japanese</a> woman who is rescued by Bae-dal and falls for him.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Jung_Tae-woo" title="Jung Tae-woo">Jung Tae-woo</a> as Chun-bae, Bae-dal's friend, something of a scoundrel but a loyal friend.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Jung_Doo-hong" title="Jung Doo-hong">Jung Doo-hong</a> as Bum-soo, a martial arts master from Bae-dal's home town who becomes a mentor to him.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Yeom_Hye-ran" title="Yeom Hye-ran">Yeom Hye-ranas</a> Circus troupe middle-aged woman</li></ul>
